<br>
The pet thing I've never heard of, but it sounds interesting. My wife and I frequently pair up in Skyfire but we usually leave the summoners alone. She engulfs and fears them and then as soon as fear breaks she gets summoned and killed. Since fear deals no damage we could attempt some experiments by pulling <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> all the way</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> to the BW zone and then fear them without engulfing. If what you say is true then so long as she deals no damage beyond what her pet does, then she will not get summoned. <p><p><font face="Arial" COLOR="blue" size="2"><b>Nefarius Frobozz, "Gnome of Action"</b><br>Devout Agnostic Magician of the 54th Trial<i><br>Member of Silmindo, Terris-Thule<br></i></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ukjeldon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kjeldon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 32<br> <font color=#333333>(5/4/01 11:58:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=210.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.iconbazaar.com/people/crit_que.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Dealing with summoning mobs 50+</span><hr size=1> As above, its all about controling agro. If you solo a good bit in your younger years. Agro will be nothing to worry about. Some monsters you may have to chain cast. At which it COULD get painful, but a nice earth pet should help that. (Not that Ive tested this.)<br>
